## Title
Vault Folder Architecture

## Recommendation Summary

### Intent Assessment
Documents the numbered directory structure from 00-meta through 09-attachments, explaining the rationale and mapping to PARA, Zettelkasten, and Topics.

### Categorization Changes
- **ZETT**: "none (status: qualifying)" → "content_stage: reference" (Structural reference documentation. Reference stage. Missing content_stage field.)
- **TREE**: "meta/pkm, meta/workflows" → "meta/beestgraph/architecture, meta/pkm" (This is core beestgraph architecture. meta/workflows is less relevant.)
- **GRAPH**: "Likely has Document node" → "Ensure edges to MOCs, Diary of Bygones, PARA Method, Zettelkasten Method, Topic Tree Organization. Vault Architecture and Numbered Directory Structure should be Concept nodes." (Central structural doc needs connections to all organizational methods.)

### Metadata Issues
Missing content_stage field. Status qualifying — should be published. Missing created_at/updated_at. IMPORTANT: The body says folders 05-08 map to PARA, but actual vault uses 05-projects, 05-areas (same prefix 05!), 07-resources, 09-archive per the Audit Playbook. This inconsistency between documented and actual folder numbers should be corrected. Also mentions obsidian-headless-cli in Connections — verify this tool still exists/is used.

